SIMPLE: scarcely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scarcely
<hw>Scarce"ly</hw>, }</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>With difficulty; hardly; scantly; barely; but
just.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With a <qex>scarce</qex> well-lighted flame.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The eldest <qex>scarcely</qex> five year was of age.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Slowly she sails, and <qex>scarcely</qex> stems the tides.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had <qex>scarcely</qex> finished, when the laborer arrived who
had been sent for my ransom.</q> <rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Frugally; penuriously.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scarcement</ent>⟦br⟧
